        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 10:37PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 1037 PM CDT/1137 PM EDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 7 miles east of Albion to
near Darmstadt to near Corydon. Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haubstadt, Boonville, Darmstadt, Spurgeon, Francisco, Winslow,
Stanley, Lynnville, Oakland City, Owensville, Somerville, Chandler,
Melody Hill, Princeton, Mount Carmel, Fort Branch, Folsomville,
Gentryville, Patoka, and Chrisney.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 69 in Indiana between Mile Markers 1 and 46.
Interstate 64 in Indiana between Mile Markers 17 and 54.
Audubon Parkway near Mile Marker 1.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT/500 AM EDT/ for
southwestern Indiana...and northwestern Kentucky.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT/100
AM EDT/ for southeastern Illinois.</instruction>
